[b]Broadening Wedge Scanner Pro[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Slides a fixed-size window of confirmed swings across the chart and fits two boundary lines — an upper line from the window's outer highs, a lower line from its outer lows — to find expanding wedges: descending broadening (both lines fall, lower faster — bullish bias), ascending broadening (both lines rise, upper faster — bearish bias), or symmetric broadening (a direction-neutral "megaphone"). Every distinct, non-overlapping valid wedge found is scored 0-100 and tracked independently until a confirmed breakout resolves it.

[b]Scoring[/b]
[list]
[*]Structure — boundary slopes match a valid broadening shape
[*]Expansion — real widening ratio end-to-start, monotonic through the midpoint
[*]Touch quality — how many of the window's highs/lows actually respect their boundary
[*]Line quality — the faster-diverging side is meaningfully faster, not just technically faster
[*]Duration — the window spans a meaningful number of bars
[/list]

[b]Features[/b]
[list]
[*]Sliding-window search across the depth range, not a fixed point count
[*]Tracks multiple simultaneously valid, non-overlapping wedges at once
[*]Live breakout tracking — either boundary breaking resolves the pattern, with a directional alert
[*]Near-miss candidate marker and score-breakdown debug table for threshold tuning
[*]Dashboard with status, active pattern count, best score, type and window size
[/list]

